HEADWORD: Trackage
<hw>Track"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of tracking, or towing, as a boat; towage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Railroads)</fld> <def>Lines of track, collectively;
<as>as, an extensive <ex>trackage</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tracker</ent>⟦br⟧
